  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "[ERC20 Token Standard](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-20) tells:\r\n> **Approval**\r\n> MUST trigger on any successful call to `approve(address _spender, uint256 _value)`.\r\n\r\nBut current ERC20 implementation emits `Approval` event on every `allowance` change. Is there any practical reason for this or just a bug?\r\n\r\nOriginal discussion started here: https://github.com/makerdao/dss/issues/76",
